X-WR-CALNAME:Central disruption
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-06-18T11:00:00&endDate=2026-06-19T10:59:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nTUBE STRIKE: Some London Underground Tube drivers are planning to take strike action on the following dates and times: From 1200 Tuesday 19 until 1159 Wednesday 20 May\, from 1200 Thursday 21 until 1159 Friday 22 May\, from 1200 Tuesday 16 until 1159 Wednesday 17 June and from 1200 Thursday 18 until 1159 Friday 19 June. On the affected Tuesdays and Thursdays\, Tube services will run normally in the morning. Disruption is expected once the strike begins\, and services are expected to finish earlier than normal. On Wednesdays and Fridays\, services are expected to start later than normal and disruption is expected to continue until midday\, when the strike ends\, but disruption is likely through the afternoon and evening.
DTEND:20260619T105900Z
DTSTART:20260618T110000Z
SUMMARY:Central: Special Service
UID:27de458f-3070-4fb3-91d3-b720819cbd8e@27de.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-05-16T00:45:00&endDate=2026-05-16T04:15:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nCENTRAL LINE: Saturday 16 May\, between 0145 and 0515\, no service between Marble Arch and Woodford / Newbury Park. Replacement bus service CL5 operates between Stratford City Bus Station (for Stratford) and Woodford via Leyton\, Leytonstone\, Snaresbrook and South Woodford. Please use Night Buses for other stations.
DTEND:20260516T041500Z
DTSTART:20260516T004500Z
SUMMARY:Central: Part Closure
